5|$|Polonium shows {{nonmetallic}} {{character in}} its <b>halides,</b> {{and by the}} existence of polonides. The <b>halides</b> have properties generally characteristic of nonmetal <b>halides</b> (being volatile, easily hydrolyzed, and soluble in organic solvents). Many metal polonides, obtained by heating the elements together at 500–1,000°C, and containing the Po2− anion, are also known.|$|R
